Definition at line 42 of file EaglePageProvider.h.

Synchronize EaglePageProvider_nextPage() and EaglePageProvider_pagesRemaining().

Definition at line 69 of file EaglePageProvider.h.

int offsetRecords

The cursor position.

An internal counter of the position of the stream. If the stream has more pages this will be incremented with each nextPage().

Definition at line 17 of file EaglePageProvider.h.

int(* pagesRemaining)(struct EaglePageProvider_ *epp)

Ask the provider if there is more data available.

This must be invoked before every nextPage() - since the stream might be variable and more data may be added to the stream while your reading from it.

Definition at line 48 of file EaglePageProvider.h.

void* records

A pointer to the actual data that will be fed into pages.

You should not rely on accessing this directly because its type and implementation will be different depending on the type of page provider. Use the appropriate methods nextPage() and pagesRemaining().

The memory for this instance variable is only managed when the page provider is a stream type.

Definition at line 37 of file EaglePageProvider.h.

int totalRecords

The total amount of records.
